HEADWORD: Doeskin
<hw>Doe"skin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The skin
of the doe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A firm woolen cloth with a smooth, soft surface like
a doe's skin; -- made for men's wear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doff</ent>⟦br⟧
